  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PeruTM10.5">
<l>valivaṇakku varaineṭuntōḷ virātaik koṉṟu vaṇṭamiḻmā muṉikoṭutta varivil vāṅki</l>
<l>kalaivaṇakku nōkkarakki mūkkai nīkkik karaṉōṭu tūṭaṇaṉṟa ṉuyirai vāṅkic</l>
<l>cilaivaṇakki māṉmariya veytāṉ ṟaṉṉait tillainakart tiruccitra kūṭan taṉṉuḷ</l>
<l>talaivaṇakkik kaikūppi yētta vallār tiritalāl tavamuṭaittit taraṇi tāṉē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>This earth is endowed with merit by the wanderings of those capable of praising,</l>
<l>with folded hands and bent heads inside Tiruccitrakūṭam in the town of Tillai,</l>
<l rend="indent">the One, who, having killed Virādha with mountain[-like] large shoulders</l>
<l rend="indent">that subdue [the foes’] power,</l>
<l rend="indent">received the striped bow that the great sage</l>
<l rend="indent">of the generous Tamil [language] gave [Him]</l>
<l rend="indent">removed the nose of the demoness whose eyes defeated the stag’s,</l>
<l rend="indent">took the life of Dūṣaṇa along with Khara’s,</l>
<l rend="indent">bent the bow [and] shot an arrow so that the deer died.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
